  "prompt": "How does one find a ghostwriter for a movie script?",
  "response": "To find a ghostwriter for a movie script, you can try several approaches:\n\n1. Professional networks\n- Writers Guild of America (WGA) website\n- LinkedIn professional networks\n- Screenwriting forums and groups\n\n2. Online platforms\n- Freelance websites like Upwork\n- Stage 32\n- Script consultant websites\n- Hollywood screenwriting job boards\n\n3. Personal recommendations\n- Ask filmmaking contacts\n- Network at film festivals\n- Seek referrals from screenwriting groups\n\n4. Professional services\n- Script consulting agencies\n- Talent agencies\n- Screenwriting workshops\n\n5. Academic/professional connections\n- Film school alumni networks\n- Screenwriting program contacts\n- Professional screenwriting associations\n\n6. Screening process considerations\n- Review writing samples\n- Check writing credits\n- Discuss experience\n- Verify genre expertise\n- Discuss confidentiality and compensation\n- Verify WGA membership or professional credentials\n\n7. Cost considerations\n- Rates typically range from $5,000-$50,000\n- Depends on script complexity\n- May involve upfront payment or percentage of potential sale\n\nImportant tips:\n- Have a clear concept\n- Sign confidentiality agreements\n- Establish clear contract terms\n- Verify writer's credibility",
